Boil a #medium size pot{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Once it comes to a rapid boil add the @Brown Basmati Rice{1/2} (rinse the rice first) and cook for ~{25%minutes}. Drain and keep to the side.

> Tip: Make sure the water is rapidly boiling to cook the rice faster.

Peel and chop the @Red Onion{1} in half lengthways before slicing into thin half moon shapes. Remove the core from the @Green Pepper{1} and slice into small bite-sized chunks. Slice the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1} widthways into really thin shreds.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #pan{} on high heat. Once hot add the pepper and cook for a few mins until slightly browned off. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Remove and keep to the side.

Add another drizzle of @olive oil{} to the pan and cook the onions for ~{8%minutes} on medium heat. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and some @pepper{}. You want to get the onions nice and soft with a little bit of colour. Add the @Mexican Spice{1/2%tsp} and the @Smoked Paprika{1%tsp} to the onions and stir for ~{1%minute}. Add the @Chopped Tomatoes{1%can} with @sugar{1/4%tsp} (if you have some) and turn the heat to medium-low. Leave to simmer for around ~{10%minutes} until the tomato sauce has thickened.

When the sauce has thickened, stir in the @Organic Black Beans{1} and the peppers and take off the heat.

Once the rice is cooked and drained, crumble the @Feta Cheese{3} into it and stir together. Grate a bit of @Lime{1/2} zest in a #bowl{} and mix together with the @Sour Cream{4} along with @lime juice{1/2%tsp}.

Put a little pile of all the ingredients into the middle of each @Super Soft Tortillas with Whole Wheat{5}. Fold the left and right hand side into the middle then roll the tortilla up.

> You can eat the tortillas straightaway, but we recommend cleaning your #frying pan{} and putting it back on high heat. Then placing your tortillas in the pan until golden and crispy on all sides. Serve with the sour cream mixture on the side - Arriba!